The purpose of this problem is to give you practical experience with the creating a Microsoft Presentation Foundation Application and Linq to access a real database

 
After you have completed the problem, you will have built a program that is a C# WPF application 
The application will have Linq code to a working database (Customers)
Your application will have WPF controls 
You will be able to view all customer records in the database table.
You will be able to add records to the database
You will be able to delete records from the database
You will be able to update records in the database.Prerequisite background
1. We are using information from chapter 9 LINQ
2. We are using information from (Visual C# 2012 chapter 22) LINQ access to Microsoft SQL database
3. We are using information from (Visual C# 2012 chapter 32) WPF applications
